{% set navbar_data = [
  {
    text: "Real-Time AI",
    url: "#!"
  },
  {
    text: "End-to-end Automation",
    url: "#!",
  },
  {
    text: "Journey-centric Delivery",
    url: "#!"
  },
  {
    text: "Low Code",
    url: "#!"
  },
  {
    text: "Multi-dimensional Power",
    url: "#!"
  },
  {
    text: "Cloud Choice",
    url: "#!"
  }
] %}

{% set navbar_content %}
  {% for item in navbar_data %}
    {% include "@bolt-components-navbar/navbar-item.twig" with item only %}  
  {% endfor %}
{% endset %}

<div class="o-bolt-wrapper u-bolt-padding-top-large u-bolt-padding-bottom-large">
  {% grid "o-bolt-grid--center o-bolt-grid--large o-bolt-grid--matrix o-bolt-grid--middle u-bolt-margin-bottom-medium" %}
    {% cell "u-bolt-width-1/1 u-bolt-width-2/3@small" %}
      <p>The Navbar component's <code>full</code> width option allows the component to span the entire page / screen's width in size -- ideal for sticky nav and overall site navigation.</p>
    {% endcell %}

    {% cell "u-bolt-width-1/1" %}
      {% include "@bolt-components-navbar/navbar.twig" with {
        title: {
          tag: "h2",
          text: "Title Text",
          icon: {
            name: "marketing-gray"
          }
        },
        content: navbar_content
      } only %}
    {% endcell %}

    {% cell "u-bolt-width-1/1 u-bolt-width-2/3@small" %}
      <p>This <code>full</code> config option for the Navbar component can be combined with the other config options available such as <code>center</code>.</p>
    {% endcell %}

    {% cell "u-bolt-width-1/1" %}
      {% include "@bolt-components-navbar/navbar.twig" with {
        title: {
          tag: "h2",
          text: "Title Text",
          icon: {
            name: "marketing-gray"
          }
        },
        center: true,
        content: navbar_content
      } only %}
    {% endcell %}
  {% endgrid %}

  {% grid "o-bolt-grid--center o-bolt-grid--rev o-bolt-grid--large o-bolt-grid--matrix o-bolt-grid--middle" %}
    {% cell "u-bolt-width-1/1 u-bolt-width-1/2@medium u-bolt-width-2/3@large" %}
      <p>The Navbar component's <code>auto</code> width option allows the component to be used in situations where it doesn't / shouldn't span the browser's entire screen-width in size (ex. in a sidebar or off-canvas nav)</p>
    {% endcell %}

    {% cell "u-bolt-width-1/1 u-bolt-width-1/2@medium u-bolt-width-1/3@large" %}
      {% include "@bolt-components-navbar/navbar.twig" with {
        title: {
          tag: "h2",
          text: "Title Text",
          icon: {
            name: "marketing-gray"
          }
        },
        full_bleed: false,
        content: navbar_content
      } only %}
    {% endcell %}

    {% cell "u-bolt-width-1/1 u-bolt-width-1/2@medium u-bolt-width-3/5@large" %}
      {% include "@bolt-components-navbar/navbar.twig" with {
        title: {
          tag: "h2",
          text: "Title Text",
          icon: {
            name: "marketing-gray"
          }
        },
        full_bleed: false,
        center: true,
        content: navbar_content
      } only %}
    {% endcell %}

    {% cell "u-bolt-width-1/1 u-bolt-width-1/2@medium u-bolt-width-2/5@large" %}
      <p>This provides maximum flexibility when coming up with creative solutions.</p>
    {% endcell %}
  {% endgrid %}
</div>



